
+-------HowTo-----------------------------------------------+
| How to use java graphs library ?                      [1] |
|   1) get the graphs.jar file                              |
|      ./java/target/graphs.jar                             |
|   2) two options :                                        |
|      2.a) add it into your CLASSPATH environment variable |
|           you do not need to do step 3)                   |
|      2.b) copy it into your project directory             |
|   3) when compiling (resp. executing), add the graphs.jar |
|      file to the javac (resp. java) binary --classpath or | 
|      -cp argument                                         |
|                                                           |
| How to compile java graphs library ?                  [2] |
|   1) get the source files                                 |
|      ./java/src/                                          |
|   2) cd into java directory                               |
|   3) launch build.sh script file                          |
|   4) if no error occured you can launch release.sh script |
|      file to create the jar file                          |
|   5) execute launch.sh to check if everything seems to be |
|      ok
+-----------------------------------------------------------+

